SIMPLE: unseal
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unseal
<hw>Un*seal"</hw> <pr>(⟦ucr⟧n*s⟦emac⟧l")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<ety>[1st pref. <ets>un-</ets> + <ets>seal</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To break or remove the seal of; to open, as what is sealed; <as>as,
to <ex>unseal</ex> a letter</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Unable to <qex>unseal</qex> his lips beyond the width of a quarter
of an inch.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To disclose, as a secret.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>The Coronation.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unseam</ent>⟦br⟧
